{"sha": "96d5dd6fca93322babc1caa531aa789f4e82ecf6", "node_id": "C_kwDOAAsO6NoAKDk2ZDVkZDZmY2E5MzMyMmJhYmMxY2FhNTMxYWE3ODlmNGU4MmVjZjY", "commit": {"author": {"name": "Matthias Kr\u00fcger", "email": "matthias.krueger@famsik.de", "date": "2023-03-20T08:46:51Z"}, "committer": {"name": "GitHub", "email": "noreply@github.com", "date": "2023-03-20T08:46:51Z"}, "message": "Rollup merge of #109170 - eggyal:xc-linux-cmake, r=Mark-Simulacrum\n\nSet `CMAKE_SYSTEM_NAME` for Linux targets\n\nWhen bootstrap compiles native dependencies like LLVM, it should set `CMAKE_SYSTEM_NAME` for the target system; otherwise cmake may not identify that it is cross-compiling.\n\nIn particular, when building a Linux rustc on a macOS host, cmake was including `-isysroot /path/to/macOS.sdk` options that caused things to break.  By setting `CMAKE_SYSTEM_NAME=Linux` when building for Linux targets, the macOS SDK is no longer passed as sysroot to the compiler.\n\nr? bootstrap", "tree": {"sha": "30cdc005fdbe24e4425748c5e802ccf91a1848c2", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/git/trees/30cdc005fdbe24e4425748c5e802ccf91a1848c2"}, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/git/commits/96d5dd6fca93322babc1caa531aa789f4e82ecf6", "comment_count": 0, "verification": {"verified": true, "reason": "valid", "signature": "-----BEGIN PGP SIGNATURE-----\n\nwsBcBAABCAAQBQJkGB17CRBK7hj4Ov3rIwAAPZ0IAAAsbP4aWNMtDcLpUBiNmPHL\npFK3l+y774E4rdXdybGX18Ebb42MMtO9K6FulEC/8jUZgl99uroXr1JiPXC+//uM\nSJNffJi2gwetEtkMOgTcOFm96whaVFeuuCZbbCJL53Omm1k6cue82tcZd9roEZAP\nCf5+uQoiW87iyuiP7c4qQvb4rV3UiZqESl6ZI3VSz5Tvpl/LNSAu3Ld2RHYov2vh\njtHyLqExuZMQhvhR4cGpZw+m4Swj+EzDP73VEFJBfrxVAYW5hEiJc13GseX6Qgx6\nz5cDR/YPqOV+QsAxUw+nkFXz4079AAfMM8S2ncMA3kAbiCcQbNFSUnFVG4tw7O4=\n=4PJC\n-----END PGP SIGNATURE-----\n", "payload": "tree 30cdc005fdbe24e4425748c5e802ccf91a1848c2\nparent e91364bcf5100017a8bd5b18cdebefdd3e5f0bb1\nparent d10b113b355a49aa2bb1552e96c48b19b7846c27\nauthor Matthias Kr\u00fcger <matthias.krueger@famsik.de> 1679302011 +0100\ncommitter GitHub <noreply@github.com> 1679302011 +0100\n\nRollup merge of #109170 - eggyal:xc-linux-cmake, r=Mark-Simulacrum\n\nSet `CMAKE_SYSTEM_NAME` for Linux targets\n\nWhen bootstrap compiles native dependencies like LLVM, it should set `CMAKE_SYSTEM_NAME` for the target system; otherwise cmake may not identify that it is cross-compiling.\n\nIn particular, when building a Linux rustc on a macOS host, cmake was including `-isysroot /path/to/macOS.sdk` options that caused things to break.  By setting `CMAKE_SYSTEM_NAME=Linux` when building for Linux targets, the macOS SDK is no longer passed as sysroot to the compiler.\n\nr? bootstrap\n"}}, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/commits/96d5dd6fca93322babc1caa531aa789f4e82ecf6", "html_url": "https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/commit/96d5dd6fca93322babc1caa531aa789f4e82ecf6", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/commits/96d5dd6fca93322babc1caa531aa789f4e82ecf6/comments", "author": {"login": "matthiaskrgr", "id": 476013, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjQ3NjAxMw==", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/476013?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/matthiaskrgr", "html_url": "https://github.com/matthiaskrgr", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/matthiaskrgr/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/matthiaskrgr/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/matthiaskrgr/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/matthiaskrgr/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/matthiaskrgr/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/matthiaskrgr/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/matthiaskrgr/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/matthiaskrgr/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/matthiaskrgr/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "committ